<div xml:id="AN1-kilavi">
    <p type="edition">
piriviṭai yāṟṟāḷāya talaimaka ṭōḻikkuc colliyatu.
   </p>
    <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">
What was spoken to the confidante by HER who did not have the strength in the time of separation.
    </p>
</div>
<div xml:id="AN1">
<p type="edition">vaṇṭupaṭat tatainta kaṇṇi yoṇkaḻa<caesura/>
luruvak kutirai maḻava rōṭṭiya<caesura/> 
muruka ṉaṟpōr neṭuvē ḷāvi<caesura/>
yaṟukōṭ ṭiyāṉaip <choice><seg>potuḷiya</seg><seg>potiṉi</seg></choice> yāṅkaṭ<caesura/>
ciṟukā rōṭaṉ payiṉoṭu cērttiya<caesura/>
kaṟpōṟ piriyala meṉṟa coṟṟā<caesura/>
maṟantaṉar kollō tōḻi ciṟanta<caesura/>
vēymaruḷ <choice><seg>paṇaittō ṇekiḻac cēeynāṭṭup</seg><seg>paṇaittōḷ ñekiḻa nāṭṭup</seg></choice><caesura/>
polaṅkala veṟukkai tarumār nilampaka<caesura/>
vaḻalpōl veṅkatir paitaṟat teṟutali<caesura/>
ṉiḻaṟēyn tulaṟiya maratta <choice><seg>varai</seg><seg>va<supplied>ṟai</supplied></seg></choice>kāy<caesura/>
paṟunīrp paiñcuṉai yāmaṟap pulartali<caesura/>
<supplied>ṉuku</supplied>neṟ poriyum vemmaiya yāvarum<caesura/>
vaḻaṅkuna riṉmaiyiṉ <choice><seg>vauvunar</seg><seg>vavvu<supplied>na</supplied>r</seg></choice> maṭiyac<caesura/>
curampul leṉṟa vāṟṟa valaṅkuciṉai<caesura/>
<choice><seg>nāriṉ</seg><seg>nārila</seg></choice> muruṅkai <choice><seg>naviral</seg><seg>virala</seg></choice> vāṉpūc<caesura/>
cūralaṅ kaṭuvaḷi yeṭuppa vāruṟ<caesura/>
ṟuṭaitiraip pitirviṟ poṅki muṉ<caesura/>
kaṭalpō ṟōṉṟala kāṭiṟan tōrē<caesura/>
</p>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent">In that place <choice><seg>full of</seg><seg>Pontini,</seg></choice> the elephants with broken tusks</l>
<l rend="indent">of Āvi with long rule in good battle, [and] of Murukaṉ, </l>
<l rend="indent">who made warriors with shapely horses run, </l>
<l rend="indent">bright anklets [and] chaplets dense so that bees settle [there], </l>
<l>the words “we won’t separate, like the stones</l>
<l rend="indent">joined together with glue by the <choice><seg>maker of little whestone”,</seg><seg>little whetstone maker”,</seg></choice></l>
<l>has he forgotten [them], friend,</l>
<l>― he who,</l>
<l>in order to bring a wealth of golden ornaments, from strange lands,</l>
<l rend="indent">while [my] superb bamboo-like bamboo shoulders become emaciated,</l>
<l rend="indent5">traversed wildernesses that appear like the sea</l>
<l>before [him], foaming with the spray of breaking waves,</l>
<l>roaring when the whirling fierce wind lifts</l>
<l>the <choice><seg>dishevelled white</seg><seg>fingery pure</seg></choice> flowers of <choice><seg>the barkless Muruṅkai tree</seg><seg>barkless Muruṅkai trees</seg></choice></l>
<l>with swaying branches on empty desert paths,</l>
<l rend="indent">as robbers doze, in the absence of anybody passing,</l>
<l rend="indent">in the heat that parches the paddy shed because of drying up,</l>
<l rend="indent">while the water ceases in mountain pools with ceasing water,</l>
<l rend="indent">the <choice><seg>slopes</seg><seg>rocks</seg></choice> with withering trees sweltering, shade dwindling,</l>
<l rend="indent2">because [sun] beams, hot like fire, scorch so that the green ceases,</l>
<l rend="indent2">so that the ground cracks.</l>
</lg>
</div>
</body>
